        <!-- Title Section -->
        <div class="section-label">Internal Note ‚Ä¢ December 2025</div>
        <h1>U.S. Securities <span>Tokenization</span></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Summary of regulatory developments around blockchain-based securities settlement in U.S. capital markets</p>

        <!-- Executive Summary -->
        <div class="exec-summary">
            <h3>What Happened & Why It Matters</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>NASDAQ filed with the SEC</strong> to offer tokenized securities trading on existing exchange infrastructure ‚Äî the first major U.S. exchange to propose this under current securities law, with no exemptions requested.</li>
                <li><strong>DTCC received SEC authorization</strong> to tokenize equities, ETFs, and U.S. Treasuries on pre-approved blockchains. DTCC holds $100T+ in assets and already processes 100K+ daily blockchain transactions via Project Ion.</li>
                <li><strong>SEC Chairman publicly endorsed</strong> tokenization as a "core feature" of U.S. markets within 2-3 years ‚Äî signaling regulatory support at the highest level for institutional adoption.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

